}})|vine-master|{{vern|vine mildew}}, {{l|en|vine-mildew}}|[[vine moth]], {{l|en|vine-moth}}\n|vine of Sodom\n|{{vern|vine-pear}}|vine-pest|vine-press|vine-prop|vine pull schemes\n|viner<!--implement-->|vine-rake|vine-rod|vinery\n|{{vern|vine sawfly}}, {{l|en|vine-sawfly}}|vine-scroll|vine-scrub,vine scrub|{{vern|vine slug}}|{{vern|vine snail}}, {{l|en|vine-snail}}|{{vern|vine snake}}|{{vern|vine sorrel}} ({{taxlink|Cissus trifoliata|species}})|{{vern|vine sphinx}}|{{vern|vine spinach}}|vine staff,vine-staff|vine-stock\n|{{vern|vine tree}}, [[vine-tree]]\n|vine-wand|vine-water|[[vine weevil]], {{l|en|vine-weevil}} ({{taxlink|Otiorhynchus sulcatus|species}})|{{vern|vine-worm}}\n|vineyard\n|vining<!--adjective, noun-->\n|{{vern|Virginia vine}}, {{l|en|Virginian vine}}\n|{{vern|watermelon vine}} ({{taxlink|Citrullus vulgaris|species}})|{{vern|water vine}}, {{l|en|water-vine}} ({{taxlink|Phytocrene|genus}})|[[wax vine]]|{{vern|white potato vine}} ({{taxfmt|Solanum tuberosum|species}})|white vine,white-vine stem|[[wild potato vine]], {{vern|wild sweet potato vine}} ({{taxlink|Ipomoea fastigata|species}})|{{vern|winter melon vine}} ({{taxfmt|Cucumis melo|species}})|{{vern|wire vine}} ({{taxfmt|Muehlenbeckia|genus}} spp.)|{{vern|with-vine}} ({{taxfmt|Elymus repens|species}})|wither on the vine|{{vern|wonga vine}}, {{vern|wonga wonga vine}} ({{taxlink|Pandorea pandorana|species}})|{{vern|wood-vine}} ({{taxfmt|Bryonia|genus}} spp.)\n|{{vern|yellow passionvine}} ({{taxlink|Passiflora lutea|species}})\n}}\n\n====Related terms====\n{{col4|en\n|provine\n|vigneron\n|vignette\n|vignoble\n|vinatorian\n|vinea\n|vineal\n|vineatic\n|viner<!--obsolete: vine-grower; from Old French-->\n|vinet\n|viny\n|wine\n}}\n* ''See also [[wine#Related terms]]''\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-see|climbing plant that produces grapes|grapevine}}\n\n{{trans-top|any plant of the genus ''Vitis''}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|лоза|f}}\n* Chichewa: {{t|ny|mpesa}}\n* Esperanto: {{t+|eo|vito}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|viiniköynnös}}\n* Georgian: {{t+|ka|ვაზი}}\n* Gothic: {{t|got|𐍅𐌴𐌹𐌽𐌰𐍄𐍂𐌹𐌿|n}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|लता|f}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|vite|m}}, {{t+|it|vitigno|m}}\n* Middle English: {{t|enm|vine}}, {{t|enm|vine-tre}}\n* Persian: {{t+|fa|رز|tr=raz}}, {{t+|fa|انگور|tr=angur}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|vid|f}}, {{t+|es|parra|f}}, {{t+|es|labrusca|f}} {{qualifier|wild vine}}, {{t|es|parriza|f}} {{qualifier|wild}}, {{t+|es|parrón|m}} {{qualifier|wild}}, {{t+|es|cepa|f}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|vin|c}}, {{t+|sv|vinranka|c}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|üzüm asması}}\n* Welsh: {{t|cy|gwinwydd|f-p}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|any similar climbing or trailing plant}}\n* Amharic: {{t+|am|ሐረግ}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|որթատունկ}}\n* Basque: {{t|eu|igokari}}\n* Bikol:\n*: Central Bikol: {{t+|bcl|balagon}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t|bg|виещо се растение}}\n* Catalan: {{t|ca|planta enfiladissa|f}}\n* Chichewa: {{t|ny|mpesa}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|grimpoplanto}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|köynnöskasvi}}, {{t+|fi|köynnös}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|grimpante|f}}\n* Georgian: {{t+|ka|ვაზი}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Kletterpflanze|f}}, {{t+|de|Ranke|f}}, {{t+|de|Schlingpflanze|f}}\n* Hawaiian: {{t|haw|lāʻau hihi}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|लता|f}}, {{t+|hi|बेल|m}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|féithleog|f}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|rampicante|m}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|蔓|tr=tsuru}}\n* Khmer: {{t+|km|លតា|tr=lea’daa}}, {{t+|km|វល្លិ}}\n* Latin: {{t+|la|vitis}}\n* Lithuanian: {{t|lt|vijoklis|m}}\n* Malayalam: {{t+|ml|വള്ളിച്ചെടി}}, {{t+|ml|ആരോഹി}}\n* Māori: {{t|mi|aka}}\n* Mongolian: {{t|mn|усан үзмийн мод}}\n* Persian: {{t+|fa|بالارونده|tr=bâlâravande}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|pnącze|n}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|cipó|m}}\n* Serbo-Croatian: {{t+|sh|loza|f}}\n* Slovene: {{t+|sl|trta|f}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|trepadora|f}}, {{t+|es|enredadera|f}}, {{t+|es|bejuco|m}}, {{t+|es|liana|f}}, {{t+|es|boqui|m}}, {{t|es|coguilera|f}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|ranka|c}}, {{t+|sv|klätterväxt|c}}, {{t|sv|slingerväxt|c}}\n* Telugu: {{t+|te|లత}}, {{t+|te|తీగ}}\n* Thai: {{t+|th|เถา}}, {{t+|th|ไม้เถา}}, {{t+|th|เถาวัลย์}}\n* Tocharian B: {{t|txb|laitke}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|sarmaşık}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t+|uk|лоза|f|tr=lozá}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|dây leo}}\n* Yoruba: {{t|yo|àjàrà}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===See also===\n* {{l|en|kudzu}}\n* {{l|en|liana}}\n* {{l|en|scrambler}}\n* {{l|en|twiner}}\n\n===References===\n* {{pedia}}\n* {{R:OneLook}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=einv|nevi|veni-|Vien|vein}}\n\n{{C|en|Grapevines|Plants}}\n\n==Catalan==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{ca-IPA}}\n* {{rhymes|ca|ine|s=2}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|ca|verb form}}\n\n# {{ca-verb form of|venir}}\n\n==Danish==\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|da|noun form|g=c}}\n\n# {{infl of|da|vin||indef|p}}\n\n==Estonian==\n\n===Noun===\n{{et-noun|vine|vinet}}\n\n# [[mist]]\n\n====Declension====\n{{et-decl-pere|vine}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|et|uduvine||haze}}\n* {{l|et|vinene||misty}}\n\n==French==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{fr-IPA|pos=v}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-WikiLucas00-vine.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Lyon>>)}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|fr|verb form}}\n\n# {{inflection of|fr|viner||1//3|s|pres|ind//sub|;|2|s|impr}}\n\n==Inari Sami==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{rfe|smn}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{rfp|smn}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|smn|noun|head=viṇe}}\n\n# {{rfdef|smn}}\n\n====Inflection====\n{{smn-infl-noun-even|viṇe}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:smn:NDS-smnfin}}\n* {{R:Álgu|17467}}\n\n==Latin==\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|la|noun form|head=vīne}}\n\n# {{infl of|la|vīnus||voc|s}}\n\n==Middle English==\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom {{bor|enm|xno|vinne}}, {{m|fro|vine}} ({{cog|fro|vigne}}), from {{der|enm|la-vul|vinia}}, from {{der|enm|la|vīnea||vineyard; vine}}. {{doublet|enm|vyny}}.\n\n====Alternative forms====\n* {{alter|enm|vin|viene|vign|vigne|veine|vyne|vyn|vyene|vygn|vygne|veyne|win|wine|wyn|wyne}}\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{IPA|enm|/ˈviːn(ə)/}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{enm-noun|vines|pl2=vinen|pl2_qual=early}}\n\n# {{senseid|enm|grapevine}} [[grapevine]]\n#* {{RQ:Wycliffe NT Lichfield|book=John|chapter=15|verse=1|leaf=51|side=v|passage=I am a verrei '''vyne''' .· ⁊ my fadir is an erþetilier{{...}}|translation=I am a true '''vine''', and my father is a cultivator{{...}}}}\n# [[vineyard]]\n\n=====Related terms=====\n* {{l|enm|vyner}}\n* {{l|enm|vynet}}\n* {{l|enm|vyneȝerd}}\n* {{l|enm|vyne-tre}}\n* {{l|enm|vynour}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n* {{desc|en|vine}}\n* {{desc|sco|vine}}\n\n====References====\n* {{R:MED Online|vīne|n.(1)|MED51176}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\nFrom {{bor|enm|fro|vigne||siege engine}}, from {{der|enm|la|vīnea}}.\n\n====Alternative forms====\n* {{alter|enm|vyne}}\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{IPA|enm|/ˈviːn(ə)/}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{enm-noun}}\n\n# {{senseid|enm|siege engine}}{{lb|enm|military}} [[siege engine]]\n\n====References====\n* {{R:MED Online|vīne|n.(2)|MED51177}}\n\n===Etymology 3===\n\n====Noun====\n{{enm-noun}}\n\n# {{alt form|enm|wyn||wine}}\n\n===Etymology 4===\n\n====Noun====\n{{enm-noun}}\n\n# {{alt form|enm|vyny}}\n\n{{c|enm|Horticulture|Plants}}\n\n==Romanian==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|ro|/ˈvi.ne/}}\n* {{rhymes|ro|ine|s=2}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n\n====Noun====\n{{head|ro|noun form}}\n\n# {{plural of|ro|vână}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n\n====Verb====\n{{head|ro|verb form}}\n\n# {{verb form of|ro|veni||3s|pres|ind}}\n\n==Spanish==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{es-pr|+<audio:LL-Q1321 (spa)-AdrianAbdulBaha-vine.wav<a:Colombia>>}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|es|verb form}}\n\n# {{es-verb form of|venir}}\n\n==Volapük==\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|vo|noun form}}\n\n# {{inflection of|vo|vin||dat|s}}"}}